{"type":"message","id":"bfb64162","parentId":"b145f7a9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:55:33.212Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zodqrmusexj8_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 2957\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1276\n[mutation proposed] research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 025513 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight creates a unified Phase 1/Phase 2 problem. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next logical step to validate this hypothesis empirically.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"amber-claw","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 2957\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1276\n[mutation proposed] research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 025513 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight creates a unified Phase 1/Phase 2 problem. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next logical step to validate this hypothesis empirically.\n","name":"powershell Bypass"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774335333210}}
{"type":"message","id":"f5eaa6cb","parentId":"bfb64162","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:55:33.214Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zodqrmusexj8_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 025415\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at the context, I need to advance the Phase 1 goal: **Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment**.\r\n\r\nThe next action from the goals is:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe insight that compression and causal discovery are the same problem is compelling. I need to start implementing the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what I have:\r\n1. Pulse logs in `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n2. The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md doc explaining the theory\r\n3. Need to implement a classifier that:\r\n   - Identifies invariant (stable, recurring) vs variant (changing) content\r\n   - Uses invariants to predict next pulse\r\n   - Meets >70% classification accuracy and >60% prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nI should create a script or document that implements the TIC experiment. Given I'm in a PowerShell environment (based on pulse.ps1), I should probably create a PowerShell script or Python script to run this analysis.\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC experiment script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant/variant\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse content\r\n4. Reports accuracy metrics\r\n\r\nI'll create `experiments/tic_experiment.ps1` or `experiments/TIC.md` with the experimental setup.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pattern, I should probably create a script that does the actual work. Let me create a Python script for the TIC experiment since Python is better suited for text processing and classification.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant structure across pulse logs and uses it to predict subsequent content. This is the concrete next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment script that analyzes pulse logs to classify invariant/variant content and predict next pulses. This implements the core Phase 1 advancement hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Tests: Compression == Causal Discovery\r\n# Goal: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Hypothesis\r\nInvariant content (stable across pulses) represents causal structure.\r\nVariant content (changing between pulses) represents temporal noise.\r\nA compressor that discovers invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n### Methodology\r\n1. Parse last N pulse logs\r\n2. Extract atomic content units (sentences, code blocks, findings)\r\n3. Classify each unit as INVARIANT (appears in ≥K pulses) or VARIANT (unique/new)\r\n4. Use invariant set to predict next pulse content\r\n5. Measure accuracy against held-out pulse\r\n\r\n### Success Criteria\r\n- **Classification:** ≥70% of content correctly tagged invariant/variant\r\n- **Prediction:** ≥60% of next pulse content correctly predicted from invariants\r\n\r\n## Initial Test Run\r\nAnalyzing: `logs/pulse_2026-03-24_025217.md` and 19 prior pulses\r\nClassification threshold: K=3 (appears in ≥3 pulses = invariant)\r\nPrediction: next_pulse = f(invariant_set)\r\n\r\n## Results Log\r\n| Date | Classification | Prediction | Status |\r\n|------|---------------|------------|--------|\r\n| TBD  | TBD%          | TBD%       | PENDING |\r\n\r\n---\r\n*Phase 1 & Phase 2 unified: Compress the invariants, discover the causation.*\r\nfile: experiments/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:54:37\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774335333212}}
