{"type":"message","id":"1741da9c","parentId":"c9c82bf4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:55:48.980Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6inidfbspr59_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 025513\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiments/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 1 is essentially complete with the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight\r\n- The next action is the TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n- This involves implementing a classifier on pulse log files\r\n\r\nThe pending task is:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist and understand their structure to implement the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nI should look at the pulse logs to understand their format and then implement the TIC classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight creates a unified Phase 1/Phase 2 problem. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next logical step to validate this hypothesis empirically.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier experiment script that will analyze pulse logs to identify invariant vs variant content patterns and test prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n## Phase 1 Advancement: Compression-Causal Duality Validation\r\n\r\n**Hypothesis:** Causal structure IS invariant structure — compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n**Success Criteria:**\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Step 1: Extract Pulse Features\r\nFrom each `logs/pulse_*.md`:\r\n- Goals mentioned (persistent vs new)\r\n- File references (repeated vs unique)\r\n- Action patterns (routine vs novel)\r\n- Insight keywords (reinforced vs first-occurrence)\r\n\r\n### Step 2: Classify Invariants\r\n- **INVARIANT:** Pattern appears in ≥3 consecutive pulses\r\n- **VARIANT:** Pattern appears in <3 pulses or changes form\r\n\r\n### Step 3: Predict Next Pulse\r\nFrom invariants in pulse N, predict:\r\n- Which goals will persist\r\n- Which files will be referenced\r\n- Which actions will repeat\r\n\r\n### Step 4: Validate\r\nCompare predictions against actual pulse N+1 content.\r\n\r\n## Implementation Status\r\n- [ ] Extract features from last 20 pulse logs\r\n- [ ] Compute invariant/variant classifications\r\n- [ ] Generate next-pulse predictions\r\n- [ ] Measure accuracy vs success criteria\r\n- [ ] Document results in `research/TIC-RESULTS.md`\r\n\r\n## Pulse Log Analysis (Last 20)\r\n```\r\nfile: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n<minimax:tool_call>\r\n- [ ] Implement pulse log feature extractor\r\n- [ ] Build invariant classifier\r\n- [ ] Create prediction engine\r\n- [ ] Run validation metrics\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe experiment will test whether identifying temporal invariants in pulse history enables accurate prediction of future pulse content, validating the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:55:32\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774335348977}}
